CORE STACK
Computer Vision (Object Detection)
 YOLOv8 (Ultralytics)
Use for:
Detect vegetation
Detect guy guard


Why?
Free + open-source
Pretrained models available
Can run locally
Fast to prototype
Install:
pip install ultralytics
OCR (Read Asset Tag)

  
EasyOCR
Use for:
Reading pole tag numbers
Why?
Free
Works offline
No API keys
Better for real-world text than Tesseract sometimes
Install:
pip install easyocr

  
Image Handling
OpenCV
Use for:
Preprocessing images before OCR
Cropping tag areas
Resizing
Converting to grayscale
OCR accuracy goes up a lot with preprocessing.
Install:
pip install opencv-python

  
Data & Logic
Pandas
Use for:
Loading GIS records
Matching pole IDs
pip install pandas

  
Prediction 
XGBoost
Use for:
Predicting risk score
Why?
Free
Fast
Works with small data
pip install xgboost

  
Dashboard
Streamlit
Use for:
Upload image
Show AI findings
Show mismatches
Show risk score
Why Streamlit?
Because:
Python-based 
Runs locally (no hosting needed)
Install:
pip install streamlit
  

Supporting Tools
  
NumPy
Needed for:
Image arrays
Model inputs
pip install numpy
  
Pillow
Handles images for Streamlit
pip install pillow

